  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_cdea887f2d4424203a16cc7aa7cf7c4c">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Various types of games ranging from historical to contemporary board and card games and puzzles. Game titles include: The Adventure Kit of Mathematics, Bingo, The Newlywed Game, Stork Bingo, Scrabble, Monopoly, Happy Families, Old Bachelor--the 90s Version of Old Maid, Flinch, Gumby Colorform Playset, Touring, The Big Board, Architector Jr., Murder at the Missions, Risk, The Fat Albert and the Cosby's Game, Sweet Valley High, African American Discovery, New Town, Marvel Superheroes, Bingo, Old Maid, travel games, Goren's Bridge for 2, Outdoor Survival, Tompkins County Trivia Game, Mental Nuts, Monopoly Deluxe Edition 2002, Monte Carlowe Casino Game Set, and Round the World with Nellie Bly. Also includes picture puzzles and jigsaw puzzles.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_a4f1ead1e9942ce0639083be9a8304c6">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Additional games include: An Historical Game of England (1804); The Historiscope, a Panorama &amp; History of America (1868); What Shall I Be? The Exciting Game of Career Girls (1966); Capital Punishment (1981); Dr. Ruth's Game of Good Sex; Public Assistance (1980) and Twinkees and Trolls. Also, an atomic bomb game from World War II, with a picture of an atomic bomb hurtling toward Japan and two pegs which the player tries to insert in the holes marked Hiroshima and Nagasaki; and La Dame de Coeur, a French sex game.</p>  </scopecontent>
